hom the Ottoman authority could trust. By focusing on Müteferrika’s western-formed mindset the book detects the influence of his printing enterprise upon the transition from scribal tradition to print culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPrintingzTurkeyxHistory. 0aPublishers and publishingzTurkeyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Turkey & Ottoman Empire.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068818440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618116192zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618116192423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618116192/original  a978-3-11-068818-4  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK